                  </hi>. I am the son of Samuel Brooks; he is a bow-string-maker, and has a factory in Three Pigeon court Angel alley, Shore ditch I left work there on the 14th of November at twelve o'clock at night and left about nine gallonss of sheeps-guts in a pail l—I came to</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183511230089"></xptr>
               <p>the factory on the following Monday morning—some tiles had then been taken off the place, and the pail and guts were gone—I informed my father, who went and found the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18351123-name-566" type="witnessName">
